item.title: CVE-2021-33842|2024-09-16T20:01:18.942Z -- circutor -- sge-plc1000
item.description: Improper Authentication vulnerability in the cookie parameter of Circutor SGE-PLC1000 firmware version 0.9.2b allows an attacker to perform operations as an authenticated user. In order to exploit this vulnerability, the attacker must be within the network where the device affected is located.

item.title: CVE-2021-33841|2024-09-16T17:59:08.672Z -- circutor -- sge-plc1000
item.description: SGE-PLC1000 device, in its 0.9.2b firmware version, does not handle some requests correctly, allowing a remote attacker to inject code into the operating system with maximum privileges.
